**Some explanations:**

To update a field you need to perform the following operations :

 1. Get the new value
 2. Get the old value 
 3. If the new value is null or is equal to the old value -&gt; done
 4. Update with the new value (and keep track of the name of the updated field)

These steps are always the same regardless of the type of the fields. What depends of the type are the &quot;Get&quot;s, the &quot;Set&quot; actions (there is technically also the &quot;is equal&quot; but since it is a method between values of the type, it is already taken care of). 

These &quot;Get&quot; and &quot;Set&quot; actions are provided as parameters ([Function][2] for the &quot;Get&quot; and [BiConsumer][3] for the &quot;Set&quot;) of the method `update` that then needs to be a [generic method][1]. 




  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/extra/generics/methods.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/function/Function.html
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/function/BiConsumer.html

